The position has the responsibility for researching, troubleshooting and supporting of multiple PeopleSoft modules for our global clients. The role of the Sr. Primary Support Engineer requires the expertise and skills to diagnose serious issues; then develop, test, package and deliver fixes for such issues in complex, integrated and highly-configured environments.

VAGA DESIGNER UX

Este(a) profissional é essencial para a construção visual de qualquer plataforma, não se limitando somente a projetos de websites, como também aplicações para desktop, web apps, banners, sistemas e até mesmo interfaces em dispositivos móveis.
Designer UX é quem realiza, principalmente, a elaboração de mapas de navegação do usuário, testes de usabilidade, criação, desenvolvimento e implementação de soluções inovadoras e atraentes, prototipação, fluxo do usuário e de processos, ligando a interação comunicativa às ideias de Design. Depois de realizados os testes, juntamente com o feedback de usuários, ele poderá também otimizar as plataformas criadas, realizando a documentação de todos os processos.

Como características pessoais, é necessário:
Excelente habilidade de design com sensibilidade para interação dos usuários;
Excelente habilidade de comunicação e apresentação de ideais;
Saber resolver problemas criativamente e de forma eficaz;
Antenado às últimas tendências, técnicas e tecnologias da área, com atualização frequente.

REQUISITOS
- 1 a 2 anos de experiência min.
- Conhecer figman ou XD Adobe.
- Ter experiência em definição de fluxos e ERP.

DIFERENCIAL
Destacam-se portfólio consistente na área, experiências sólidas, Motion Design e edição de vídeos, ilustração, graduação em Design Gráfico, Design Digital, ou áreas afins e especializações na área de UX.

React Native Developer

We are looking for a React Native developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the
iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as
well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure. Building a
product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to
perfection is required.

Responsibilities

• Translating UI designs and UX wire-frames into high-quality codes
• Build pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms (IOS and Android)
• Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both platforms
• Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks for performance that feels native
• Optimizing components for maximum performance
• Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality
• Transition existing React web apps to React Native
• Release applications to the Apple and Google Play stores.
• Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create a web application run on
multiple platforms via Slack, Zoom and email
• Work with modern tools including Jira, Confluence, GitHub, BitBucket, Google Docs, etc.

Skills

• Firm grasp of the JavaScript (TypeScript or ClojureScript) language and its nuances, including
ES6+ syntax
• Knowledge of functional and object-oriented programming
• Ability to write well-documented, clean Javascript code
• Rock solid at working with third-party dependencies and debugging dependency conflicts
• Familiarity with native build tools, like XCode, Gradle, Android Studio, IntelliJ, etc
• Understanding of REST APIs, GraphQL, the document request model, and offline storage
• Experience with automated testing suites (unit test) like Jest, Jasmine, Mocha, etc
• Experience with end to end testing suites (e2e test) like Detox, Cypress, etc
• Proficiency with modern development tools, like Babel, Webpack, and Git
• Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
• Full life cycle app development experience as a solo developer or in a small team environment
• Additional prior native mobile programming experience will be a plus
• Familiarity with one of the popular frameworks like Vue, Angular, Svelte is a plus

VAGA DESIGNER UX

Este(a) profissional é essencial para a construção visual de qualquer plataforma, não se limitando somente a projetos de websites, como também aplicações para desktop, web apps, banners, sistemas e até mesmo interfaces em dispositivos móveis.
Designer UX é quem realiza, principalmente, a elaboração de mapas de navegação do usuário, testes de usabilidade, criação, desenvolvimento e implementação de soluções inovadoras e atraentes, prototipação, fluxo do usuário e de processos, ligando a interação comunicativa às ideias de Design. Depois de realizados os testes, juntamente com o feedback de usuários, ele poderá também otimizar as plataformas criadas, realizando a documentação de todos os processos.

Como características pessoais, é necessário:
Excelente habilidade de design com sensibilidade para interação dos usuários;
Excelente habilidade de comunicação e apresentação de ideais;
Saber resolver problemas criativamente e de forma eficaz;
Antenado às últimas tendências, técnicas e tecnologias da área, com atualização frequente.

REQUISITOS
- 1 a 2 anos de experiência min.
- Conhecer figman ou XD Adobe.
- Ter experiência em definição de fluxos e ERP.

DIFERENCIAL
Destacam-se portfólio consistente na área, experiências sólidas, Motion Design e edição de vídeos, ilustração, graduação em Design Gráfico, Design Digital, ou áreas afins e especializações na área de UX.

We are looking for a React Native developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the
iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as
well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure. Building a
product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to
perfection is required.

Responsibilities

• Translating UI designs and UX wire-frames into high-quality codes
• Build pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms (IOS and Android)
• Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both platforms
• Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks for performance that feels native
• Optimizing components for maximum performance
• Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality
• Transition existing React web apps to React Native
• Release applications to the Apple and Google Play stores.
• Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create a web application run on
multiple platforms via Slack, Zoom and email
• Work with modern tools including Jira, Confluence, GitHub, BitBucket, Google Docs, etc.

Skills

• Firm grasp of the JavaScript (TypeScript or ClojureScript) language and its nuances, including
ES6+ syntax
• Knowledge of functional and object-oriented programming
• Ability to write well-documented, clean Javascript code
• Rock solid at working with third-party dependencies and debugging dependency conflicts
• Familiarity with native build tools, like XCode, Gradle, Android Studio, IntelliJ, etc
• Understanding of REST APIs, GraphQL, the document request model, and offline storage
• Experience with automated testing suites (unit test) like Jest, Jasmine, Mocha, etc
• Experience with end to end testing suites (e2e test) like Detox, Cypress, etc
• Proficiency with modern development tools, like Babel, Webpack, and Git
• Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
• Full life cycle app development experience as a solo developer or in a small team environment
• Additional prior native mobile programming experience will be a plus
• Familiarity with one of the popular frameworks like Vue, Angular, Svelte is a plus

React Native Developer

We are looking for a React Native developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the
iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as
well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure. Building a
product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to
perfection is required.

Responsibilities

• Translating UI designs and UX wire-frames into high-quality codes
• Build pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms (IOS and Android)
• Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both platforms
• Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks for performance that feels native
• Optimizing components for maximum performance
• Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality
• Transition existing React web apps to React Native
• Release applications to the Apple and Google Play stores.
• Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create a web application run on
multiple platforms via Slack, Zoom and email
• Work with modern tools including Jira, Confluence, GitHub, BitBucket, Google Docs, etc.

Skills

• Firm grasp of the JavaScript (TypeScript or ClojureScript) language and its nuances, including
ES6+ syntax
• Knowledge of functional and object-oriented programming
• Ability to write well-documented, clean Javascript code
• Rock solid at working with third-party dependencies and debugging dependency conflicts
• Familiarity with native build tools, like XCode, Gradle, Android Studio, IntelliJ, etc
• Understanding of REST APIs, GraphQL, the document request model, and offline storage
• Experience with automated testing suites (unit test) like Jest, Jasmine, Mocha, etc
• Experience with end to end testing suites (e2e test) like Detox, Cypress, etc
• Proficiency with modern development tools, like Babel, Webpack, and Git
• Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
• Full life cycle app development experience as a solo developer or in a small team environment
• Additional prior native mobile programming experience will be a plus
• Familiarity with one of the popular frameworks like Vue, Angular, Svelte is a plus

We are looking for a React Native developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the
iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as
well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure. Building a
product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to
perfection is required.

Responsibilities

• Translating UI designs and UX wire-frames into high-quality codes
• Build pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms (IOS and Android)
• Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both platforms
• Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks for performance that feels native
• Optimizing components for maximum performance
• Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality
• Transition existing React web apps to React Native
• Release applications to the Apple and Google Play stores.
• Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create a web application run on
multiple platforms via Slack, Zoom and email
• Work with modern tools including Jira, Confluence, GitHub, BitBucket, Google Docs, etc.

Skills

• Firm grasp of the JavaScript (TypeScript or ClojureScript) language and its nuances, including
ES6+ syntax
• Knowledge of functional and object-oriented programming

• Rock solid at working with third-party dependencies and debugging dependency conflicts

React Native Developer

We are looking for a React Native developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the
iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as
well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure. Building a
product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to
perfection is required.

Responsibilities

• Translating UI designs and UX wire-frames into high-quality codes
• Build pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms (IOS and Android)
• Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both platforms
• Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks for performance that feels native
• Optimizing components for maximum performance
• Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality
• Transition existing React web apps to React Native
• Release applications to the Apple and Google Play stores.
• Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create a web application run on
multiple platforms via Slack, Zoom and email
• Work with modern tools including Jira, Confluence, GitHub, BitBucket, Google Docs, etc.

Skills

• Firm grasp of the JavaScript (TypeScript or ClojureScript) language and its nuances, including
ES6+ syntax
• Knowledge of functional and object-oriented programming
• Ability to write well-documented, clean Javascript code
• Rock solid at working with third-party dependencies and debugging dependency conflicts
• Familiarity with native build tools, like XCode, Gradle, Android Studio, IntelliJ, etc
• Understanding of REST APIs, GraphQL, the document request model, and offline storage
• Experience with automated testing suites (unit test) like Jest, Jasmine, Mocha, etc
• Experience with end to end testing suites (e2e test) like Detox, Cypress, etc
• Proficiency with modern development tools, like Babel, Webpack, and Git
• Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
• Full life cycle app development experience as a solo developer or in a small team environment
• Additional prior native mobile programming experience will be a plus
• Familiarity with one of the popular frameworks like Vue, Angular, Svelte is a plus

Redux, Hulks.

React Native Developer

We are looking for a React Native developer interested in building performant mobile apps on both the
iOS and Android platforms. You will be responsible for architecting and building these applications, as
well as coordinating with the teams responsible for other layers of the product infrastructure. Building a
product is a highly collaborative effort, and as such, a strong team player with a commitment to
perfection is required.

Responsibilities

• Translating UI designs and UX wire-frames into high-quality codes
• Build pixel-perfect, buttery smooth UIs across both mobile platforms (IOS and Android)
• Leverage native APIs for deep integrations with both platforms
• Diagnose and fix bugs and performance bottlenecks for performance that feels native
• Optimizing components for maximum performance
• Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality
• Transition existing React web apps to React Native
• Release applications to the Apple and Google Play stores.
• Collaborate with a team of developers and designers to create a web application run on
multiple platforms via Slack, Zoom and email
• Work with modern tools including Jira, Confluence, GitHub, BitBucket, Google Docs, etc.

Skills

• Firm grasp of the JavaScript (TypeScript or ClojureScript) language and its nuances, including
ES6+ syntax
• Knowledge of functional and object-oriented programming
• Ability to write well-documented, clean Javascript code
• Rock solid at working with third-party dependencies and debugging dependency conflicts
• Familiarity with native build tools, like XCode, Gradle, Android Studio, IntelliJ, etc
• Understanding of REST APIs, GraphQL, the document request model, and offline storage
• Experience with automated testing suites (unit test) like Jest, Jasmine, Mocha, etc
• Experience with end to end testing suites (e2e test) like Detox, Cypress, etc
• Proficiency with modern development tools, like Babel, Webpack, and Git
• Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
• Full life cycle app development experience as a solo developer or in a small team environment
• Additional prior native mobile programming experience will be a plus
• Familiarity with one of the popular frameworks like Vue, Angular, Svelte is a plus

Através do Instituto Barigüi são realizadas mais de 1.000 coletas nas concessionárias e destinados mais de 525 toneladas de resíduos por ano. Toda a renda gerada pelos resíduos é revertida em bolsas de estudos em cursos profissionalizantes para jovens de baixa renda.

E não paramos de pensar no futuro. Criamos o Banco Bari, um banco digital que nasce com o propósito de mudar a relação que o brasileiro tem com seu dinheiro, com soluções completas de conta, crédito e investimentos.

Grupo Barigüi, o futuro nos move.

Para compor nosso time, estamos buscando Desenvolvedor(a) Fullstack (.net core/Angular).

Buscamos pessoas preocupadas em desenvolver sistemas sustentáveis, que sejam fáceis de manter, escaláveis e que causem orgulho aos seus criadores.

Nossos principais desenvolvimentos são em:
- Angular 8+
- .NET Core (C#)
- Bancos relacionais
- Scrum

O que buscamos?
- Experiência em implementação de APIs Restfull

Conhecimento não obrigatórios:

• Ser um profissional Data-driven (troughput, burndown, CFD);
• Identificar possibilidades e necessidades de melhoria no processo e aplicá-las;
• Criar reports sobre o andamento das sprints das diversas squads e envio aos stakeholders;
• Retirar impedimentos, agendar todos os eventos scrum e ser um facilitador;

Requisitos e qualificações:
• Ter experiencia de trabalho com múltiplas squads;
• Desejável experiencia de 3 anos ou mais como Scrum master;
• Desejável certificação de Scrum master;
• Técnica de mensuração e previsão de entrega/resultado;
• Fácil comunicação seja com time de desenvolvimento, product owner e demais stakeholders na empresa;
• Ter trabalhado como Scrum master em uma StartUp seria um diferencial;
• Fácil convívio no dia a dia de trabalho;
